spans.text: The vast immeasurable realms of space Over which Messiah drives his flaming car To that bright region
the Muse , Her feeble wing all damp with earthly dew , Soar to that bright empyreal , where around , Myriads of angels , God's perpetual choir , Hymn Halelujah's
albeit unused To tread poetic soil

At once shall rise , Whom distant ages to each other's sight
the great With costly pomp and aromatic sweets

are they Who sunk an aged father to the grave : Or with unkindness hard and cold disdain Slighted a brother's sufferings : — Here are they Whom fraud and skilful treachery long secured ; Who from the infant virgin tore her dower , And eat the orphan's bread : — who spent their stores In selfish luxury ; or over their gold Prostrate and pale adored the useless heap

What punishment ! for that the Almighty Will Has hid from mortal eyes : and shall vain man With curious search refined presume to pry Into thy secrets , Father

With humble patience all thy works adore , And walk in all thy paths
in the place of heaven's Eternal King
For them in vain Alternate seasons
who fought beneath The banner of Jehovah , and defied Satan's united legions
